  "text": "GamingYour guide to 2026’s game release datesMay 11, 2025, 3:00 PM UTCImage: Rockstar GamesMichael McWhertor is a journalist with more than 17 years of experience covering video games, technology, movies, TV, and entertainment.When Rockstar Games delayed Grand Theft Auto 6 into 2026, it likely came as a big relief to publishers who had anything on their slate for the back half of 2025. But 2026 is already shaping up to be an exciting, crowded year of big game releases, even without GTA 6.In addition to Rockstar’s ambitious new crime epic, we can expect Playground Games’ new Fable (finally!), Housemarque’s Returnal follow-up Saros, FromSoftware’s The Duskbloods, the return of Capcom’s Onimusha franchise, and (at least) two long-awaited new franchise entries from Nintendo: Rhythm Heaven Groove and Tomodachi Life: Living the Dream.Beyond sequels, there are plenty of promising original games on the horizon, like role-playing game SacriFire, Warren Spector’s stealth-action PvPvE game Thick As Thieves, and Animal Crossing-but-make-it-vampires indie Moonlight Peaks.Game release dates are always in flux, though, so Polygon’s guide to the new video games coming out in 2026 will be regularly updated with new titles, release dates, and (inevitable) delays.New video game releases coming in 2026MayGrand Theft Auto 6 (PS5, Xbox Series X) — May 262026 video games with no release dateBlackfrost: The Long Dark 2 (PC)Cthulhu: The Cosmic Abyss (PC, PS5, Xbox Series X)Decapolice (PC, PS4, PS5, Switch)Enter the Gungeon 2 (PC, Switch 2)Fable (PC, Xbox Series X)Ikuma - The Frozen Compass (PC, PS5, Xbox Series X)Lords of the Fallen 2 (PC)Moonlight Peaks (PC)Onimusha: Way of the Sword (PC, PS5, Xbox Series X)Prince of Persia: The Sands of Time (TBA)Rhythm Heaven Groove (Switch)SacriFire (PC, PS4, PS5, Switch, Xbox One, Xbox Series X)Samurai Pizza Cats: Blast from the Past (PC, consoles TBA)Saros (PS5)Screamer (PC, PS5, Xbox Series X)Star Wars Zero Company (PC, PS5, Xbox Series X)